          "payload": "node.web.detail"
        },
        "renderShape": {
          "kind": "markdown"
        },
        "markdown": "# Getting Started\n\nTwilite is easiest to learn in three moves:\n\n1. Understand the shelf.\n2. Learn the graph-native vocabulary.\n3. Bootstrap your first LLM session.\n\nThis graph points at the modern public lessons that teach those steps."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "getting-started-intro",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Choose Your First Path",
      "root": true,
      "position": {
        "x": 80,
        "y": -1220
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-getting-started"
        },
        "markdown": "## Choose Your First Path\n\n- Open **Start Here** if you want the official map.\n- Open **About Twilite** if you want orientation before authoring.\n- Open **Bootstrap Your LLM** if you are ready to teach an agent the current mutation contract.\n- Open **Basic Primitives** when you want declaration, markdown, port, and portal explained clearly.\n\nThis graph replaces the older launcher-style document with direct links into the current tutorial shelf."
      }
    },
